there are still Rodman level rebounders but fewer big guys (effing huge) like Shaq or Robinson

David Robinson make Giannis look skinny .... Shaq make Embiid look average and portly.

it's still a relatively remarkable feat but let's be real it's a lot easier when everyone shooting threes and there's no Shaqs and Robinsons in the paint

snippet.textDisplay: The real challenge in today's era is to accumulate 200+ steals or 300+ blocks in a season rather than triple-doubles. It used to be the norm for leaders of those categories until the new millennium. When Draymond can lead the league w/ 2.03 spg in 2017 and Davis w/ 2.57 bpg in 2018 (both all-time lows), something's just not right on the defensive end. Though the league average for offensive rebounds have also been at an all-time low in recent years.
